Functions

calc_rich <- function(data, col_start, col_end) {
  columns <- c(col_start:col_end)
  subset_data <- data[, columns]
  positive_columns_per_row <- rowSums(subset_data > 0)
  return(positive_columns_per_row)
}

calc_abun <- function(data, col_start, col_end) {
  columns <- c(col_start:col_end)
  subset_data <- data[, columns]
  total <- rowSums(subset_data)
  return(total)
}

simpsons_diversity <- function(data, col_start, col_end) {
  counts <- as.numeric(row[col_start:col_end])
  counts <- counts[!is.na(counts)]
  n <- sum(counts)
  if (n == 0) return(0)
  proportions <- counts / n
  return(1 - sum(proportions^2))
}

shan_diversity <- function(df, species_cols) {
  # Subset the dataframe to select only the columns with species counts
  species_data <- df[, species_cols]
  
  # Apply the Shannon's diversity formula to each row of the species data
  shannon_index <- apply(species_data, 1, function(counts) {
    total_count <- sum(counts)
    proportions <- counts / total_count
    
    # Shannon's diversity index calculation
    proportions <- proportions[proportions > 0] # remove zeros to avoid log(0)
    -sum(proportions * log(proportions))
  })
  
  return(shannon_index)
}

Repeated measures ANOVA

options(scipen = 999)

data <- data |> 
  mutate(
    month = as.numeric(format(as.Date(paste0(Date, "-01")), "%m")),
    season = case_when(
      month %in% c(10, 11, 12, 1, 2, 3) ~ "Winter",
      month %in% c(4, 5) ~ "Spring",
      month %in% c(6, 7, 8, 9) ~ "Summer",
      TRUE ~ NA_character_
    ),
    yst = as.numeric(format(as.Date(paste0(Date, "-01")), "%Y")) - 2011
  )

data$Year <- year(data$Date)
# Step 1 is to create a dataset with only repeated points so I'm going to do the Spring samples
rep.data <- data[data$season=="Spring",]
rep.data <-rep.data |> select(Date, Year, BLOCK, Fire, abundance, simp_div, shan_div, richness)

Reduce Climate covariates to tmean, tdmean and ppt

Add the previous samples Abundance as a covariate

data <- data |>
  arrange(BLOCK, Fire, Date) |>
  group_by(BLOCK, Fire) |>
  mutate(lag.abun = lag(abundance))

Linear Models Comparison

Information Theoretic Approach

Create 10 Models with less than 10 covariates each with a hypothesis as to why that would be a an appropriate model

Abundance

## Fire needs to be rmoved from the zero inflation in all instances because of the impossible s.e. of the coefficient

set.seed(4)

hist(data$abundance)

data <- na.omit(data)

# The random effect in the zero inflation is causing issues so I've removed it

abun.null <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~  1 + (1|BLOCK), 
                     zi=~ 1,
                     family = "truncated_nbinom2") # Null Model

abun.global <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ ppt + lag.ppt + tmean + lag.tmean  + Fire + (1|BLOCK),
                     zi=~ ppt + lag.ppt + tmean + lag.tmean  + Fire,
                     family = "truncated_nbinom2")# Hyp: All factors contribute to rodent abundance
summary(abun.global)

abun.fire <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ Fire+ (1|BLOCK), 
                     zi=~ Fire,
                     family = "truncated_nbinom2") # Hyp: Fire is the main driver of rodent abundance through vegetation removal
# Remove model

abun.current <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ ppt + tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                        zi=~ ppt + tmean,
                      family = "truncated_nbinom2")                                             # Hyp: Current weather conditions drive rodent abundance

abun.lag <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ lag.ppt + lag.tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                    zi=~lag.ppt + lag.tmean ,
                      family = "truncated_nbinom2")                                             # Hyp: Previous years weather drives rodent abundance

abun.ppt <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ lag.ppt + ppt+ (1|BLOCK),
                    zi=~ lag.ppt + ppt,
                      family = "truncated_nbinom2")                                             # Hyp: Precipitation drives rodent abundance
# Remove model

abun.temp <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ tmean + lag.tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                     zi=~ tmean + lag.tmean ,
                     family = "truncated_nbinom2")    # Hyp: Temperature drives rodent abundance

abun.fire.ppt <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ ppt * Fire + lag.ppt * Fire+ (1|BLOCK),
                         zi=~  ppt * Fire + lag.ppt * Fire,
                         family = "truncated_nbinom2")                        # Hyp: Interaction between fire and precipitation drives rodent abundance
#remove

abun.fire.temp <- glmmTMB(data = data, abundance ~ Fire * tmean + Fire * lag.tmean+ (1|BLOCK),
                          zi=~ Fire * tmean + Fire * lag.tmean ,
                        family = "truncated_nbinom2")                           # Hyp: The interaction between fire and temperature drives rodent abundance
# Remove

abun.sel <- model.sel(abun.null, abun.current, abun.lag, abun.global, abun.temp, 
                      abun.fire, abun.ppt, abun.fire.ppt, abun.fire.temp)

##Richness

hist(data$richness)

rich.null <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ 1 , 
                     family = "compois") # Null Model

rich.global <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ ppt + lag.ppt + tmean + lag.tmean + Fire,
                      family = "compois") # Hyp: All factors contribute to rodent richness

rich.fire <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ Fire, 
                     family = "compois") # Hyp: Fire is the main driver of rodent richness through vegetation removal

rich.current <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ ppt + tmean,
                      family = "compois")   # Hyp: Current weather conditions drive rodent richness

rich.lag <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ lag.ppt + lag.tmean,
                      family = "compois")   # Hyp: Previous years weather drives rodent richness

rich.ppt <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ lag.ppt + ppt,
                      family = "compois")     # Hyp: Precipitation drives rodent richness

rich.temp <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ tmean + lag.tmean, 
                     family = "compois")      # Hyp: Temperature drives rodent richness

rich.fire.ppt <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ ppt * Fire + lag.ppt * Fire,
                         family = "compois")     # Hyp: Interaction between fire and precipitation drives rodent richness

rich.fire.temp <- glmmTMB(data = data, richness ~ Fire * tmean + Fire * lag.tmean ,
                        family = "compois")                         # Hyp: The interaction between fire and temperature drives rodent richness

rich.sel <- model.sel(rich.null, rich.global, rich.fire, rich.current, rich.lag,
                      rich.ppt, rich.temp, rich.fire.ppt, rich.fire.temp)

rich.sel

# Calculate 95% confidence intervals manually
gb.sh.coefs <- data.frame(
  term = rownames(gb.sh.coefs),
  estimate = gb.sh.coefs[, "Estimate"],
  conf.low = gb.sh.coefs[, "Estimate"] - 1.96 * gb.sh.coefs[, "Std..Error"],
  conf.high = gb.sh.coefs[, "Estimate"] + 1.96 * gb.sh.coefs[, "Std..Error"]
)

gb.sh.coefs
# Filter coefficients where confidence intervals do not cross 0
gb.sh.coefs_filtered <- gb.sh.coefs[gb.sh.coefs$conf.low > 0 | gb.sh.coefs$conf.high < 0, ]

custom_labels <- list(
  BRTE = paste0("BRTE\nR = ", round(rsquared["BRTE"], 2)),
  abundance = paste0("abundance\nR = ", round(rsquared["abundance"], 2))
)

# Generate the plot with custom labels
gb.abun.sem.plot <- lavaanPlot(
  name = "semabun",
  sem.abun.fit,
  coefs = TRUE,
  stand = TRUE,        # Include standardized coefficients if needed
  node_options = list(shape = "box", fontname = "Helvetica"),
  edge_options = list(color = "black"),
  labels = custom_labels
)

# Print the plot
gb.abun.sem.plot
